title: Grateful Dead Live at Music Hall on 1976-06-12
description:
Set 1

Samson & Delilah, Row Jimmy, The Music Never Stopped, Brown Eyed Women, Big River, Looks Like Rain, Friend Of The Devil, Lazy Lightning > Supplication, High Time

Set 2

The Wheel, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed-> Let It Grow-> Drums-> Let It Grow-> Wharf Rat-> Comes A Time-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Around & Around, E:Sugar Magnolia-> E:U.S. Blues-> E: Sunshine Daydream

FM Broadcast WBCN Boston

reviews.review_text: Best AUD I like this version better than CM version (please no offense intended). Its a bit too bright and grates on the ears.... this version is smooooth!   Great effort Mr. Berger whoever you are and thanks! Will most certainly do search for your other downloads.

YOU WERE GOOOOOOOOOOOOONE!!! Looks Like Rain is a hit or miss for me, but this version is a hit for sure! In fact, I often skip LLR, but this one sets the benchmark pretty high. Donna Jean sounds wonderful here, which is somewhat a rarity. Thanks to Jimmy & Rob for putting out a gem! Fantastic sound quality and gnar setlist. It'll make you feel like you are front center!
Billy's birthday If this day was actually Bill Kreutzmann's birthday as Bobby announces after Samson and Delilah, the date on this concert is incorrect.  It would be on May 7th.

Bob is often announcing that it's a birthday He's even announced that it was both drummers' birthdays one show in the Spring, April maybe(I don't remember which year).

Great show, though.
just great now this is what ya call a great show,great sound wish I had some visuals to go along with these serious tunes!!!thanks to all the kind folks who make all this happen,peace&love people...
